a comedy of manners twenty plays and the social history of the everyday in 19th century rio de janeiro center for latin american studies jump to navigation stanford university center for latin american studies search this site home events a comedy of manners twenty plays and the social history of the everyday in 19th century rio de janeiro a comedy of manners twenty plays and the social history of the everyday in 19th century rio de janeiro tuesday november 1 2011 12 15pm 1 05pm this talk will introduce the study of nineteenth century drama as a source for social history it will also explore the way dramatic categories are useful for thinking about society with particular emphasis on staging dialog and character triads the potential utility of computational approaches such as network analysis and topic modeling will be addressed the plays are all comedies so the subject matter should not be inherently boring zephyr frank is associate professor of history and director of the spatial history project at stanford university he received his ph d from the university of illinois in 1999 professor frank's research interests include the social history of brazil latin american economic history wealth and inequality geographical information systems gis terrain of history and spatial history http www stanford edu group spatialhistory index htm l he is the recipient of the dean's distinguished teaching award 2008 zephyr frank associate professor department of history stanford university bolivar house 582 alvarado row attachment size frank pdf 634.16 kb last updated january 25 2012 11 58am calendar main menu about degree programs visiting faculty & scholar programs grants & fellowships people events newsletter giving to clas secondary menu stanford home ica clasp login contact stanford university center for latin american studies bolivar house 582 alvarado row stanford ca 94305 usa phone 650.723 4444 fax 650.723 9822 stanford university terms of use copyright complaints
